<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-740-764  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 740 764.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  August 6 1990 v7 n30 p19(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Cahners-Ziff Publishing Associates LP 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Interphase software package offers Unix system managers moreoptions for disk storage. (Interphase Corp.'s Softarray for VME)(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bowen, Ted Smalley.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Interphase Corp. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    INPH.andO;Product:   Softarray for VME (Utility program) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionNetwork Management SoftwareDisk StorageUNIX.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Interphase software package offers Unix system managers more options for diskstorageandM;DALLAS -- Interphase is bringing sophisticated storage utilities to Unix witha software package for its SCSI host adapter products that allows systemmanagers to perform scanning, balanced striping and mirroring of disksubsystems.andM;Softarray for VME can be configured to perform any combination of threeseparate disk functions, according to company officials.andM;Disk mirroring lets users automatically copy files to single or multipledrives.andP;  Data to be mirrored can be specified in order to conserve diskspace, the officials said.andM;Balanced striping distributes data across multiple drives and allowssimultaneous access of files on different disks, they said.andM;Disk spanning, well-suited to data-intensive applications like video imagingor complex spreadsheets, combines data from multiple disks for use as thoughit were stored on a single, large disk, officials said.andM;The software currently supports Sun-3 and Sun-4 Sparc systems.andM;Interphase has no plans to port the software to RISC/Ultrix, though it isconsidering such a move, said Ernest Godsey, the company's vice president ofmarketing.andM;&quot;The port would make sense.andP;  To date, Interphase has no adapters working onDEC machines, but it would make sense to look at a DEC workstation thatsupports VME,&quot; he said.andM;Softarray will be available next month and is priced from $3,900 to $4,790.andM;Interphase Corp. is located at 13800 Senlac Drive, Dallas, TX 75234 (214)919-9000.andO;</TEXT></DOC>